## Lesson Criteria

3. Proposed Lesson Title: Properly Utilizing Modern Language Association (MLA) and American Psychological Association (APA) Format
4. Lesson Abstract:

To inform students on using the proper formatting for their essay or research paper. Basically a guideline for these formatting.

5. A short description of the situation/need that your lesson responds to (consider details of purpose, audience, context):

It will be a guideline for students of Pierce College to utilize when they are creating their essay or a research paper for their respective classes.
Many classes utilize the MLA format such as English, History and even within the STEM field requires their student create a typed report, while research heavy courses such as Chemistry and Biology. Though many have never heard of the APA formatting because most schools primarily focus only on the MLA format and fail to guide their students on the basic information for the APA format.


6. Learning Outcomes of Tutorial (between 2-3):

After completing this tutorial students:
* Knowing the difference between the Modern Language Association format and the American Psychological Association (APA) format.
* To have the proper set-up when utilizing either MLA or APA formatting for their respective papers.

7. Course most relevant to your tutorial (if any): English 101 or any course that asks students to write an essay or a research paper.

8. Discipline/Research Area most relevant to your tutorial? 

Example - Humanities / Social Sciences / Natural Sciences / Physical Sciences 

This tutorial is relevant to multiple disciplines.

9. Intended Submission Date:

I'll have an initial draft of this complete by Sunday, Feb. 2. Final version by Feb. 5

10. Lesson will use open technology and data at no cost to the reader?

Yes. Can use Microsoft Word(free download using student email), Google Docs(Free, but will require a Google Account) and any writing applications.

